STEP 3 — Controller: detect marker, emit separate SSE event
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In app/controllers/chat_controller.py, locate the static-output-node
handling code (where node return-value messages are yielded as chunk
events for the static_output_nodes list).

ADD detection logic: when the static message contains a
[[FORM_WIDGET:<json>]] marker, split the message into two parts:
  - The text BEFORE the marker → emit as a normal chunk event.
  - The marker payload → parse the JSON inside, emit as:
        data: {"type": "form_widget", "form": <parsed_json>}
  - Anything AFTER the marker → emit as another chunk event (if
    non-empty).

Implementation sketch (adapt to actual streaming code):

    import re, json
    FORM_MARKER_RE = re.compile(r"\[\[FORM_WIDGET:(.*?)\]\]", re.DOTALL)

    def _emit_with_form_widget(full_text: str):
        """Yields SSE event dicts: chunk before, form_widget, chunk after."""
        match = FORM_MARKER_RE.search(full_text)
        if not match:
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": full_text}
            return
        pre = full_text[:match.start()]
        post = full_text[match.end():]
        raw_json = match.group(1)
        try:
            form_obj = json.loads(raw_json)
        except Exception as e:
            # Malformed form JSON: fall back to plain chunk so user
            # still sees the text; log the error.
            print(f"[FORM-WIDGET] JSON parse error: {e}", flush=True)
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": full_text}
            return
        if pre.strip():
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": pre}
        yield {"type": "form_widget", "form": form_obj}
        if post.strip():
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": post}

When yielding events for a static node's output (inside the SSE
streaming loop), if the message text contains the form marker, run
it through _emit_with_form_widget and yield each piece. Otherwise
yield as normal.

This must be applied in BOTH stream_chat_with_orchestrator and
